================================================================
PRACTICAL 10(c) - Demonstrate the Use of Publish Utility
================================================================

DIFFICULTY: Easy

WHAT YOU WILL DO:
You will publish a UiPath project to UiPath Orchestrator 
(or publish locally as a NuGet package).

--- WHAT IS PUBLISH? ---
  Publishing packages your UiPath workflow into a .nupkg file 
  and uploads it to Orchestrator (or a local feed).
  From Orchestrator, the robot can be scheduled and run on any machine.

--- STEP-BY-STEP INSTRUCTIONS ---

PRE-SETUP (First-time only):

Step 1: Create a free UiPath Cloud account:
  - Go to: https://cloud.uipath.com
  - Click "Sign Up" → use your email to register.
  - Once logged in, you'll see the Orchestrator dashboard.

Step 2: Connect UiPath Studio to Orchestrator:
  - In UiPath Studio → top right corner → click your profile icon 
    or "Sign In"
  - Sign in with your cloud.uipath.com account.
  - Studio will automatically connect to your Orchestrator.

--- PUBLISHING YOUR PROJECT ---

Step 3: Open any project in UiPath Studio 
  (use the Practical_10a project or any earlier one).

Step 4: In the top ribbon, click the "PUBLISH" button.
  (It's in the Design or Home ribbon, usually has a cloud/arrow icon)

Step 5: The Publish dialog opens. You'll see:

  PACKAGE PROPERTIES:
  - Package Name: auto-filled with your project name (e.g., Practical_10a)
  - Package Version: 1.0.0 (you can change this)
    - Increment for updates: 1.0.1, 1.0.2 etc.

  PUBLISH TO:
  - Select "Orchestrator Tenant Processes Feed" 
    (this publishes to your cloud Orchestrator)
  OR
  - Select "Custom URL" and use a local path to save the .nupkg file locally.

Step 6: Click "PUBLISH".
  - UiPath packages your workflow.
  - A success message appears: "Package successfully published."

Step 7: Verify in Orchestrator:
  - Go to https://cloud.uipath.com → Your Tenant → Packages
  - You should see your published package listed there.

Step 8: Create a Process from the Package:
  - In Orchestrator → Automations → Processes → click "+"
  - Select your published package → click Create.
  - Now you can schedule it to run at specific times!

--- ALTERNATIVE: PUBLISH LOCALLY ---

Step 9: If you don't want to use cloud:
  - In Publish dialog → Publish To → Custom URL
  - Enter a local folder path: C:\Users\YourName\Desktop\MyPackages
  - Click Publish.
  - A .nupkg file is created in that folder.
  - This can be deployed on any UiPath Robot manually.

--- HOW TO RUN A PUBLISHED PACKAGE ---

Step 10: In Orchestrator → Jobs → Start Job
  - Select your Process.
  - Click "Start" → the robot runs the workflow.

Step 11 (Run locally from package):
  - Open UiPath Assistant (system tray icon)
  - Your published package should appear.
  - Click Play/Run to execute it.

