EXTRA NOTES FOR PRACTICAL 10:
================================================================
- Log Message levels: Trace < Info < Warn < Error < Fatal
  In production, typically log Info for milestones and Error for failures.
- Screenshots are helpful for audit trails — save them with timestamps 
  so you can review what the robot saw at each step.
- State Machine vs Sequence vs Flowchart:
    Sequence    → linear steps (one after another)
    Flowchart   → branching logic (if/else paths)
    State Machine → complex workflows with multiple stable states
  Use State Machine when your process has clearly defined modes/phases.
- When publishing, always update the version number (1.0.0 → 1.0.1) 
  so Orchestrator knows it's a new version.
- Publishing to Orchestrator is what makes UiPath truly enterprise-grade — 
  you can schedule, monitor, and manage robots from a central dashboard.
